The paper deals with information transmission over a channel, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of sparse graphs and iterative decoding also suggests a possible connection to network information theory (cs.NI) and sparse signal processing (cs.SI). The mention of time offset and spatial coupling may indicate a potential application in multimedia communication (cs.MM). Finally, the use of error correction decoding suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
